<title>BELGIUM: Italy plan sees 3.0 pct '97 deficit, 2.8 pct in 98.</title>
<headline>Italy plan sees 3.0 pct '97 deficit, 2.8 pct in 98.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-07-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Italy's convergence programme -- its efforts to consolidate public finances ahead of economic and monetary union (EMU) -- forecasts a 3.0 percent deficit in 1997, dipping to 2.8 percent in 1998, EU sources said on Friday.  </p>
<p>The sources said the convergence plan, based on 1.2 percent growth this year, rising to 2.0 percent in 1998, forecast the deficit dropping to 1.8 percent of Gross Domestic Product by 2000.</p>
<p>The EMU convergence plan is expected to be discussed at a meeting of EU finance ministers in Brussels on Monday.</p>
